Nev's Ted Talk

Most of my self expression is in the form of creativity. In order to e= xpress who I truly am I use personal art forms to feel whole.

I love to paint and draw in order to express myself in more of an arti= stic and colorful form.

Memories hold a special place in my heart...they are snapshots of what= could be the happiest moments of my life...Without them I don't think I wo= uld be able to love things in life as much as I do right now.

My life is in all sorts of chaos so I'm constantly in need of an esc= ape. However, while I may feel like the matter will run wild without contro= l, here are some simple things that I love that keep me sane and enjoying l= ife.

.

.

.

.

.

This universe right here is a universe I've lived in my whole life. = Ever since I was little, I just loved the idea of fantasy

and the possibility of becoming something superhuman. Of course as a= little kid, dreaming of having superpowers and other worldly skills

was almost expected. However, coming from a little girl? That was a = little peculiar. Thanks to my dad, I became the "son" he always wanted, jus= t with feminine features.

Moving on to the next simple happiness...cartoons. I love watching c= artoons. Whether it be shows or movies or shorts, I love watching them.

I remember when I was a kid I would watch all of these and I wouold = be in my own little happy place as I watched them.

Still to this day I'm like a little kid again when these shows come = on. I know all the theme songs and the little catch phrases of my favorite = characters.

Genuinely, I feel like this is part of who I am as a person internal= ly, and without this I wouldn't be living my life to the fullest.
